remarks: An identity law for the non-logical predicate, which combines ~ elequ1 and ~ elequ2 .  For the analogous theorems for class terms, see ~ eleq1 , ~ eleq2 and ~ eleq12 .  (TODO: move to main part.)  (Contributed by BJ, 29-Sep-2019.)
statement: bj-elequ12 $p |- ( ( x = y /\ z = t ) -> ( x e. z <-> y e. t ) ) $.
